In this free 75-minute online class, actors read and perform monologues for feedback (or just watch), and I cover a lot about choosing monologues, including 

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you

‚Ä¢ Where to look

‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material

‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions

‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire

‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing

‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues

‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

SUNDAY OCTOBER 5 | 12noon‚Äî1:15pm Eastern

RESERVE | classes@monologueaudition.com

Can‚Äôt do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about upcoming classes and free events

KAREN KOHLHAAS is an Atlantic Theater Company director, teacher and founding member. She was voted Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading teacher by Backstage readers. Her book THE MONOLOGUE AUDITION is recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on Acting.

items.text:
So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran‚Äôs Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann‚Äôs Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro‚Äôs Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane‚Äôs costumes for years! 

https://2025screamfest.eventive.org/films/68d1b14f6ac811912ea77b5c?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAR6Vy5trrNroF8v33cSuHpp_m2mf0qAtnnMljE9_T7BIh64lBOdHCOJWfuCTlQ_aem_eM-d05jAN52my1WjOr_zoQ

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I‚Äôm a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I‚Äôm looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I‚Äôm not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I‚Äôm eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I‚Äôm excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I‚Äôm incredibly proud of them.

I‚Äôm looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK‚Äôs vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I‚Äôm actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

topComments.text:
For the love of all that is holy, pleeeeeeease be careful about giving out your information so freely. Whilst most are legitimate your will just invite the creepy ones in and it's v easy to get conned.
Just some general questions so folks can actually guide you in the right direction.

Do you have any formal training, like performance based, college, workshops etc?
The standard Do you have a Spotlight account?
Do you have any experience in performance/ acting either amateur or pro?

Please be safe ok, there are far too many people who would happily take advantage.
Also headshots should generally ve in colour, CDs don't like black and white anymore. There's more on that but start with thd basics first. Best of luck üëç ‚ú®Ô∏è
Look a little like young avril leviegne üôå

CASTING CALL/ NON-UNION 

Casting Russian speaking roles in the short anti-war film 'During Winter, I Thought of My Father' written and directed by Danill Vasilyev. 

Please submit resume, headshot(s), and demo reel (if applicable) to duringwinter26@gmail.com to receive sides. 

Audition submission deadline: OCTOBER 18, 2025

Character descriptions below: 

ARTYOM

Russian speaking man, early 20s.

Description: Having seen the horrors of war firsthand, this young man became a conscientious objector who deserted the war. And despite paying a high price for his decision, losing a leg to frostbite, Artyom remains entrenched in his anti-war beliefs. A bright young

man from a middle-class family, who loves poetry and shoemaking, Artyom uses every ounce of his physical and mental might to get back to his family. 

VLADIMIR 

Russian speaking man, 50s-60s. 

A staunch patriot who was once a soldier too. A decorated one, whose pride in his heroic exploits for the Motherland could be felt from afar. But now, the old man stands alone. No family, no friends, no backing from the state which he holds so dear. His only son died

in a war years ago. All that‚Äôs left is the inextinguishable belief in his national identity, which has been built from years of tradition and pride. 

Rate: Unpaid, travel and food will be provided as well as top billing credits and IMDB credit.

**Casting Call ‚Äî vertical advertisement and reels (Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre)**

Hello everyone!

We are casting talent for vertical ads and reels to promote our clinic‚Äôs largest annual event.

**Roles Needed**

1 male + 2 female talents

Age range: 25‚Äì35

Ethnicity: Caucasian or East Asian

English: native fluency required

Preferred (not required): experience in social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

**Project Details**

Deliverables: 3 vertical videos (ads/fun reels)

Shoot Duration: 3‚Äì3.5 hours (approx., minor fluctuations possible)

Dates: Shooting between October 8‚Äì10 (exact date TBD)

**Compensation**

$300 flat rate

1 selected treatment (BBL or PicoWay, value $500)

**How to Apply**

Headshot

Resume

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out. Thank you all!

items.text:
In Living Colored Inc, a 501c3 social justice theater casting 2 Males and 1 Female. 25-45 

Performances are in November in Educational Settings for talkback audiences.

Fort Collins.

It is a satirical comedy about 4 white woke people creating a play explaining Thanksgiving to middle school students. Without offending Native Americans.

Larissa FastHorse is the first Native American to have a play produced on Broadway. 

There will be a cast -audience talkbacks led by A Lakota Woman.

"Should THANKSGIVING be a National Holiday or a National Day of Mourning?

Rehearsals start 13th of October. Tues-Friday.

We will schedule when we have cast availability.

Rehearsals are 2 hours.

The running time of the piece is 75 minutes.

Performances are the 10th, 11th, 12 of November 

Front Range Community College 

11-1.   With student Talk back 

Campuses in Fort Collins, Boulder, Westminster.

Performances 14th 15th of November Foco Cultural Enrichment Center 7:00pm  

With Audience Talk back

All Saints Episcopal Church in Loveland 

November 22nd 7:00 performance 

We comply with a Colorado Theater Standards

Pay is 500.00. 

Contact Michael Anthony Tatmon 

mat@inlivingcolored.com

Text 970-714-6534 personal 

970-820-7264 Business

items.text:
*FUNDET! 

Jeg s√∏ger en hundeejer med en s√∏d familiehund (golden retriever, labrador, den slags, gerne i en lys farve) der kunne have lyst til at have deres hund med i nogle reklamebilleder/film der fremh√¶ver sommerhushygge i Blokhus üòäü¶Æüì∑ 

Vi laver nemlig nogle optagelser i Blokhus mandag-onsdag, hvor vi gerne vil have nogle scener med en hund. Det drejer sig om et par timer, gerne tirsdag eftermiddag, men andre tidspunkter er ogs√• mulige, og det er kun hunden der skal v√¶re med. Hunden skal agere sammen med en skuespilsfamilie. 
**Vi har 1500kr til betaling for dette.**

Skriv gerne en kommentar, send mig en besked eller mail p√• daniel@24copenhagen.dk, hvis du er interesseret.

God s√∏ndag!

Exciting News! Following the incredible success of our award-winning short film 'The Hit' at the Short Film Festival Manchester, Marble Academy and Solefuge Media Productions are thrilled to announce auditions for our upcoming low-budget short film, ‚ÄòHotel Rent,‚Äô set to film early next year.

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals. 
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you‚Äôre passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you! 
Please send us a direct message or an email to marbleacademy@hotmail.com. Share a bit about yourself, the role that excites you the most, and what draws you to that character.
Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don‚Äôt forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can‚Äôt wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

items.text:
Christmas Panto Casting Call 

Troubadour Productions (TIE and care homes shows for over 20 years) are casting three actors to tour schools and some care homes in London and South East in December.

There will be four days rehearsal (probably late November) plus approx. 16 tour days in December 2025 with this multi-roling, musical production of "Beauty and the Beast."

At least one member of the cast **must** be a car owner/driver to ‚Äúdrive‚Äù the tour so car owners/drivers will have a slight advantage in the casting.

Ideally, actors should be able to live at home and commute daily to an agreed pick up point. At the end of the day the driver will then return the actors to a mutually convenient drop off point.

Each actor will receive a flat fee of ¬£1400 and the driver will receive an extra ¬£320.00 (¬£20 per day) for driving the tour. The driver will have **all** petrol paid.

The Roles

Beauty

Ideally Female. Should be an experienced singer and to be able to dance or move well. Beauty is an intellectual, very kind and helpful. She is close to her father and will do anything for him.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume and singing reel please

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

Louis/Nannette

This is a multi-roling opportunity. A versatile performer required to play Beauty's father, Louis Dubois and the housekeeper in the Beast's castle, Nanette. An actor who is capable of creating different characters by using different voices and ways of moving. Louis should preferably be played with a slight French accent. He is hardworking and a single father. Nanette can be played as a 'dame' character, very flamboyant. A comedy role. There is also a chicken in the production, which may be performed by this actor. The chicken doesn't speak, just clucks.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume/voice reel

Required Skills:

 

The Beast/Monsieur Livre

A versatile performer to play the Beast and Monsieur Livre, the librarian who hopes to win Beauty's heart. Any age or ethnicity. We perform to schools and care homes, and in some of these venues, the Beast may need to be toned down and maybe more comical than angry. In some other shows, the Beast can show their anger and frustration by shouting and making the audience jump. The Beast also has a softer side when he gets to know his 'prisoner', Beauty. The Beast wears a wig with horns, with the face uncovered. Monsieur Livre only appears at the start of the show. He is very persistent. Can be played for laughs. It is important that the actor can create two very different characters by changing voices and movement. There is also the part of Alouette, the chicken, which could be portrayed by this actor. Skin character experience preferred, but not absolutely necessary. The chicken has no lines, but is very expressive.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

The Beast/Monsieur Livre

A versatile performer to play the Beast and Monsieur Livre, the librarian who hopes to win Beauty's heart. Any age or ethnicity. We perform to schools and care homes, and in some of these venues, the Beast may need to be toned down and maybe more comical than angry. In some other shows, the Beast can show their anger and frustration by shouting and making the audience jump. The Beast also has a softer side when he gets to know his 'prisoner', Beauty. The Beast wears a wig with horns, with the face uncovered. Monsieur Livre only appears at the start of the show. He is very persistent. Can be played for laughs. It is important that the actor can create two very different characters by changing voices and movement. There is also the part of Alouette, the chicken, which could be portrayed by this actor. Skin character experience preferred, but not absolutely necessary. The chicken has no lines, but is very expressive.

Required Media: Headshot/Photo, Cover Letter, Resume

Required Skills:
* Voice Style: Singing
* Dance: Movement

 

 

 

Dates & Locations

Rehearsals  4 days (non-consecutive) between November to early December in Milford, South Guilford.

Tour runs 10-23 Dec. (Sundays are off) in South London, Hampshire, Surrey, Middlesex, Sussex and Essex, England. Note: There may be some additional dates added if production gets busier. The actors will tour from their homes and meet up with the actor or driver to perform.

Additional: At least one of the team needs to be a driver who has their own car, and is willing to use it as a company vehicle. Troubadour productions pay for all petrol in advance. An additional fee of ¬£20 per day (for use of car and driving) will be paid to the driver for performance days.

 

Auditions will be on Zoom or other virtual platforms. Production will want to see a 2-minute modern monologue. This can be targeted to the panto job or can be a piece they already know, but no Shakespeare or restoration comedy please.

We would also would like to hear a song sung to a backing track as a reel. Preferably musical theatre or possibly nostalgic pop. Music is heavily featured in our shows, and we use backing tracks, so it is important that we know you can sing to them accurately. Production shall start to see auditionees from 6 Oct. onwards.

Special Instructions:

For consideration, talent must note in the submission where they are based. This is very important when assessing for possibility of actors being able to meet up. If talent has any friends of relatives in any of the above areas, also state those towns as it may increase the likelihood of being chosen for an audition. Production doesn't have multiple teams touring different parts of the UK, just casting the one team of three for London and Home Counties.

Our actors will need a current and enhanced DBS certificate, but we will help you apply for and we will pay for one if needed.

If interested in applying please e-mail a cv, headshot and singing reel to a backing track please with answers to the following questions:

1)     Do you drive

2)     Do you have a car that you could use for the tour

3)     Where are you based (please state the name of the town or borough (of London)

4)     Do you have a DBS (We will get you one if not!)

Please e-mail applications to
tom@troubadourproductions.co.uk

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we‚Äôre on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

üìç Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
üìÜ Contract: December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£20 per hour

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Basic script work and immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Confident group singing of children‚Äôs Christmas songs

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, in a beautifully themed setting. 

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

Tue, Dec 2 ‚Äì 1:30 PM to 7:00 PM

Thu, Dec 4 ‚Äì 1:30 PM to 6:00 PM

Tue, Dec 9 ‚Äì 10:30 AM to 5:00 PM

Tue, Dec 16 ‚Äì 10:30 AM to 7:00 PM

Fri, Dec 19 ‚Äì 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

Sat, Dec 20 ‚Äì 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: MOTHER CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

items.text:
Lagos Nigeria 3 month contract üá≥üá¨ 

We are casting for a 3 month contract in Lagos, Nigeria. The engagement runs from early November through the end of January, working four nights per week in a nightclub setting.

We are looking for acts that are beautiful, elegant, and unusual.

Rigging is available.

We are particularly interested in:

Unusual LED acts
Foot archery acts
Unique or rare performance styles (fire can be used indoors)

Contract details:

Return flights provided
Working visa arranged
Accommodation provided in a secure villa (with tennis courts and swimming pool)
Driver included
Meals provided on work nights

If you have availability and an act you‚Äôd like us to consider, please comment in the thread below with your act details and a link or video.

Please do not send direct messages as these will not be responded to.

Thank you.

items.text:
**It's all about pure acting: playing the theme!**
***Secure your place and the early bird price until 15 October.***

3 x online workshops and 2 x individual coaching sessions with Christine Schmalor.

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I‚Äôve been training with Steve Eastin and it‚Äôs honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You‚Äôve seen this guy, he‚Äôs in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he‚Äôs teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just‚Ä¶ different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It‚Äôs not gonna be for everyone but if you‚Äôre someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you‚Äôre just along for the ride, this is that.

It‚Äôs rooted in Charles Conrad‚Äôs whole ‚Äúchoiceless awareness‚Äù thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure ‚Äúbeats‚Äù land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you‚Äôre curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything‚Äôs filmed so you‚Äôre used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They‚Äôre small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn‚Äôt still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it‚Äôs a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

**Hello to all the actors, aspiring actors, and curious creatives out there‚Äî this one‚Äôs for you!**

 

I‚Äôm a Berlin-based director and teacher launching a small actor training space called **Studio LeBolt**, and I‚Äôm offering **a 2-day** **monologue workshop in English** this September.

 

It‚Äôs a supportive space for anyone ‚Äî beginner or experienced ‚Äî looking to reconnect with acting, build confidence, and develop a strong audition-ready piece. Whether you‚Äôre returning to performance, building your showreel, or just want to explore something new‚Äî you‚Äôre welcome.

 

My work is rooted in embodiment, presence, and, most of all, play. I‚Äôd love for you to join us!

**Hello to all the actors, aspiring actors, and curious creatives out there‚Äî this one‚Äôs for you!**

 

I‚Äôm a Berlin-based director and teacher launching a small actor training space called **Studio LeBolt**, and I‚Äôm offering **a 2-day** **monologue workshop in English** this September.

 

It‚Äôs a supportive space for anyone ‚Äî beginner or experienced ‚Äî looking to reconnect with acting, build confidence, and develop a strong audition-ready piece. Whether you‚Äôre returning to performance, building your showreel, or just want to explore something new‚Äî you‚Äôre welcome.

 

My work is rooted in embodiment, presence, and, most of all, play. I‚Äôd love for you to join us!

dates: September 6 & 13 (13:00‚Äì17:00)

**Early bird sign up only until Aug. 14**

items.text:
üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Student Short Film (UNPAID)

Production Title: Baggage

Role: Protagonist ‚Äì Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th ‚Äì 19th September

Location: Berlin

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

üìß If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)‚Äì kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)‚Äì ahadg8@gmail.com

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

items.summary:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Sir Percy Shorter - chairman of the BMA, quite upper class and not too tall (Mid 40s+

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall

Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 

Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.

Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 

The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

***CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT FILM!!!***

***UNPAID & NON-UNION***

Location: Vancouver, BC

Film Dates: November 14th, 15th, & 16th with 2 rehearsals to be scheduled after casting

Casting "Confession", a student short film set in the late 1950s about a closeted devout Catholic who confesses his secret love for his priest during confession, only to discover the priest feels the same way.

Father Elias D'Arcy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic priest who has been the head of Jacob‚Äôs church for a few years now, developing a close relationship with his parish. He came from a poor family, the child of Irish immigrants and the eldest of 6, he‚Äôs always had a nurturing nature to him and often helped others to the detriment of his own mental capacity. A closeted homosexual, Elias has delved deep into his religion and joined the priesthood to stave off any romantic connection, unwilling to come to terms with his sexuality.

Jacob McCarthy (white male, 25-35) - A devout Catholic and closeted gay man, his struggles with his raised religion and his sexuality being the catalyst for his story. He forced himself to marry a girl he was raised going to church with to promote a sense of normalcy and to please his family as the eldest child and only son expected to carry on the family name and reputation. He's unhappy with the life he chose to live for other people, feeling as though no one really knows him for who he truly is.

Actors will be compensated with a copy of the film, credit, and a meal every day of filming.

For audition scheduling and sides, please contact a.culp@infocusfilmschool.com

üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Student Short Film

Production Title: Baggage

Director: Kole Jackson 

Role: Protagonist ‚Äì Old Man

Requirement: Male actor in his 50s or 60s, preferably with a beard. Tall and skinny physique.

Shooting Dates: 18th ‚Äì 19th September

As this is a passion-driven student short film, the role is unpaid, but catering will be provided throughout the shoot days.

Synopsis:

In a world where emotional burdens are physical baggage, an old man struggles to carry his load through a park. He longs to climb a sunlit hill but is held back by his heavy suitcases. He repeatedly rejects the help of a mysterious, baggage-free blonde man who offers him a pair of scissors to cut the rope binding him to his past. After a failed attempt to build a shelter from his bags and a collapse that leaves him injured, the old man finally accepts the scissors. Realizing he has the power to choose his path, he cuts the rope, freeing himself from his burden. The blonde man vanishes, and the old man, now unencumbered, finally climbs the hill, symbolizing his newfound freedom.

üìß If interested, please reach out to:

Kole Jackson (Director)‚Äì kole.jackson.m@gmail.com

Ahad Khan (Assistant Director)‚Äì ahadg8@gmail.com

NOW CASTING ‚Äì ‚ÄúPLUS ONE‚Äù 

Black Is a Status Productions & B. Golden Films are casting for our upcoming feature, filming late November ‚Äì early December in Denver.

**Casting Calls - Standard Posting Format**

***CU Denver Student Film Casting Call***

Title: **Wolf Tickets**

Genre: Drama, True Crime

**Logline:** A florist becomes convinced that her boyfriend, an ex-felon, poses a deadly threat to her and her unborn child, sparking a Rashomon-style tale of paranoia, alienation, and tragedy.

**Synopsis:** A pregnant woman, Vivienne, is murdered by her lover, Anthony, an ex-con with a dark past. Through two distinct narratives, it is revealed how this tragedy came to be. Vivienne‚Äôs perspective reveals how fear and miscommunication can distort our perceptions; over the course of two months, we see Antony quickly becoming the monster that he once was. Meanwhile, Antony‚Äôs story exposes the devastating consequences of alienation and desperation

Main Roles: 

**Vivienne: **Vivienne is the protagonist of Wolf Tickets. A brown, female, florist in her early 30s. She fits the ‚Äúbroken optimist archetype. In her past, she had a brief fling with her employee, Anthony, an ex-convict. After experiencing a major epiphany stemming from the news that she‚Äôs pregnant, she begins to distance herself from Anthony - the result is catastrophic and leads to her eventual death.

**Anthony: **Anthony is the antagonist of Wolf Tickets. A male ex-convict in his early 30s is employed at a flower shop. He fits the ‚Äúdreamer bound by reality‚Äù archetype. Anthony exudes charm but struggles to adapt to life outside of prison, finding solace in his relationship with Vivienne. After parting ways with her, Anthony begins to feel increasingly isolated and lost. With no clear direction or confidence, he‚Äôs suddenly overcome with the urge to repeat his past mistakes.

Writer/Director: Daniel Moreno

Producer: Emily Ball

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: For more information or questions prior to auditions, please email Emily at tvdinnerstudios25@gmail.com

Run Time: 8 Minute Short Film

Compensation: Unpaid

Additional Compensation: Meals Provided, Film Credit, & Copy of Final Cut 

Union Status: Non-Union

items.text:
Web series titled Buried Lies, set in the United Kingdom, which explores life-changing secrets, intense emotions, and the raw truth people hide. Each episode revolves around characters confronting their past through confessions that affect their lives and the people around them.

We are seeking talented, expressive individuals ready to take on a variety of dramatic roles. All nationalities are welcome to apply.

PROJECT DETAILS:

Title: BURRIED LIES (Web Series)

Genre: Drama / Thriller

Locations:

London

Manchester

Liverpool

Edinburgh

Shooting Dates:

October 27th ‚Äì December 5th, 2025 (Flexible schedules possible) This is Tentative dates for Episode One Only

Usage: Web series for online streaming platforms and promotional content

Payment: ¬£200 ‚Äì ¬£350 per shooting day, depending on role and experience

MAIN CHARACTERS & EXAMPLES OF CONFESSIONS:

1. Emma (28) ‚Äì A young woman who confesses to having sabotaged her best friend‚Äôs career out of jealousy.

2. David (45) ‚Äì A corporate executive who admits to embezzling funds to cover personal debts.

3. Sophie (22) ‚Äì A college student revealing her involvement in an illegal online scheme that endangered others.

4. Mark (35) ‚Äì A father confessing to hiding the truth about a child‚Äôs paternity.

5. Leila (30) ‚Äì A mysterious woman confessing that she witnessed a hit-and-run accident and stayed silent.

6. James (40) ‚Äì A detective forced to confess to using illegal means to close a high-profile case.

7. Clara (50) ‚Äì A mother disclosing that she manipulated family inheritance to favor one child over another.

8. Ali (33) ‚Äì A young man confessing to secretly living a double life to escape financial troubles.

9. Nina (25) ‚Äì A nurse who reveals covering up a medical mistake that led to a patient‚Äôs death.

10. Supporting Roles: Friends, colleagues, strangers, investigators, and family members deeply affected by the confessions.

EXAMPLES OF CONFESSIONS IN THE SERIES:

"I let my friend take the fall for a crime I committed."

"I have been living a lie for the past five years to protect my reputation."

"I once stole confidential data from my employer for personal gain."

"I am not the biological parent of the child I raised as my own."

"I witnessed a murder but didn‚Äôt report it because I was too scared."

"I have been in contact with a dangerous person despite knowing the risks."

WHO CAN APPLY:

All nationalities

Age 18 ‚Äì 55

Prior acting experience preferred but not mandatory

Comfortable performing intense, dramatic scenes

Willing to travel within the UK to shoot in different locations

Available for full shoot dates or specific days as needed

TO APPLY:

Send your portfolio, recent photograph, showreel (if available), and contact information to:

Email: annasiller88@gmail.com 

Auditions will start from October 11th, 2025. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted directly.

items.text:
üì£üé¨ Casting Call ‚Äì Short Mockumentary Film 

We are casting for ‚ÄòA Race with Ian Hitchworth‚Äô, a 3-minute mockumentary short film made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 3rd November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:ÔøΩIan Hitchworth, son of a respected track runner, was once a rising sprint star. Years later, he resurfaces in a humiliating viral TikTok, and a small documentary crew captures his desperate bid to matter again‚Äîculminating in a shambolic charity race. Told in a deadpan, mockumentary style, the film mixes awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability as Ian‚Äôs arrogance clashes with his insecurities.

Roles:
Ian Hitchworth (Lead)ÔøΩ25, male. Wannabe track star with inflated self-belief and fragile confidence. To the camera, he‚Äôs arrogant, overconfident, and insists on being taken seriously ‚Äî but cracks show through awkward silences and moments of panic. Actor must have strong comedic timing, improvisational instincts, and be comfortable with physical comedy (running, awkward costume, frustrated energy). Needs to balance deadpan humour with flashes of real vulnerability.

Interviewer (Supporting)ÔøΩAny age/gender. Calm, inquisitive presence behind the camera, provoking Ian with offhand questions and blunt corrections. Think Nick Broomfield style: slightly awkward, matter-of-fact, not intentionally funny but often humorous through honesty. Delivery should be dry and understated. Voice-only, but may appear briefly on camera.

Race Official / Athletes (Supporting & Extras)ÔøΩ18‚Äì40, any gender. Includes a race official who ushers Ian onto the track (Small Speaking Role), plus authentic-looking athletes for the race sequence. Non-speaking, but must look natural on a track.

Apply by: 27th Ocotber 2025ÔøΩTo Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

sharedPost.text:
I‚Äôve been a model and actor for over 30 years, and as a certified mindset coach, I‚Äôve also had the privilege of helping my daughter strengthen her mindset and grow her career with co-star, supporting, and supporting lead roles in projects for Paramount +, CBS, Hallmark, and more. Most recently, she appears as Rachel in Amazon Prime‚Äôs Top 10* *show* The Runarounds*.

Ôªø

I've been asked a lot over the years to share my experience and help other parents and young actors along on their acting journeys; that‚Äôs why I‚Äôm hosting a **free webinar on October 19** where you'll learn:
* Mindset strategies I taught my daughter (and use with my actor clients)
* The realities of building a career in acting‚Äîwhat most people *don‚Äôt*tell you
* The pros and cons of pursuing an acting degree
* Strategies we've used to open up audition and booking opportunties
* PLUS: get the inside scoop as my daughter shares her experience on *The Runarounds*: from first audition to being on set.

üéüÔ∏è Don't wait! Get all the details and save your spot here ‚Üí [[Register Now]](https://campaign-statistics.com/link_click/e9VEqJ-gpxZ2D6-4ysUg9/a85533005915d0327bef8a6796583a43)

Ôªø

üìÖ **Date: October 19, 2025 **

üïî **Time:** **4:00pm-5:30pm EST**

Ôªø

While this webinar is geared towards young actors & their parents, **actors of all levels **will benefit from this session. We will have an open, honest conversation that gives you clarity, direction, and encouragement as you navigate the acting journey.

Ôªø

Hope to see you there!

**Looking for 4 actors/actresses**

Hey everyone! 
We‚Äôre looking for **4 people who‚Äôd like to act** in a **camera and directing exercise** at our film school.
No previous experience needed, just enthusiasm and a willingness to collaborate.

**What it‚Äôs about:**
We‚Äôll be working on **short dialogue scenes**, each focused on **a specific emotion**. The exercise will explore **camera movement** and how actors and directors adapt to each other, just like in a film, but with short and experimental scenes.

The scenes can be performed in **English or German**, depending on what you feel most comfortable with.

üóì **Date:** October 16th
üïô **Time:** 10:00‚Äì16:00
üìç **Location:** FilmArche 

It‚Äôll be a fun and creative day of learning and collaboration.
If you‚Äôre interested or know someone who might be, send me a message!

Statisten gesucht!

F√ºr eine Musical Show am Samstag, 21. M√§rz 2026 im Kurhaus Bad Herrenalb werden Statisten im Alter von 16 - 99 gesucht.

Die Statisterie wird mit kleinen Schauspieleinlagen, sowie Bewegungssequenzen in die Produktion integriert sein.

Gezeigt werden Ausschnitte aus Tanz der Vampire, K√∂nig der L√∂wen, Mamma Mia, Aladdin, The Greatest Showman, Grease u.v.m.

Die Proben finden 1x w√∂chentlich in Bad Herrenalb bei Karlsruhe statt.

Die Leitung des Showprojekts hat Sandra Maria Germann, die das Musical Ensemble Dance Charisma leitet und seit vielen Jahren national und international als Musicaldarstellerin, Schauspielerin und Choreographin t√§tig ist.

Wir freuen uns auf rege Teilnahme von ambitionierten Schauspielern und T√§nzern (m/w/d).

Infos & Anmeldung unter 0176 - 39 61 45 60 oder info@dance-charisma.de

 (c) Bernd Hentschel

items.text:
The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Elizabeth Line Station / Free Parking)

Unpaid charity production

If you think you can step in and save the show then please get in touch asap - email casting@brooksidetheatre.com or PM me

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

#castingcall #casting #addamsfamilymusical #musicaltheatre #stage #stageshow

items.text:
CASTING CALL 

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production 

Project Type: UCF BFA Short Film 

Union Status: Non-Union 

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected 

Shooting Dates: TBD 

Shooting Location: Orlando area 

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her. 

This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production. 

Character Breakdowns: 

MONOMAY: Female, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants. 

JASON: Male, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma. 

FAN CLUB: Any gender, 18+ (must be able to pass as a teenager), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention. 

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

OR

Fill out this Google form: 
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeN2krq62Mec2KpTeJrleyIirLMgRBfIJkdh2N6B6q_VwMk3Q/viewform?usp=dialog

Exciting News! Following the incredible success of our award-winning short film 'The Hit' at the Short Film Festival Manchester, Marble Academy and Solefuge Media Productions are thrilled to announce auditions for our upcoming low-budget short film, ‚ÄòHotel Rent,‚Äô set to film in Manchester early next year.

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals. 
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you‚Äôre passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you! 
Please send us a direct message or an email to marbleacademy@hotmail.com. Share a bit about yourself, the role that excites you the most, and what draws you to that character.
Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don‚Äôt forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can‚Äôt wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

sharedPost.text:
@everyone 
Recently we have been working on our showreel and headshot package as a means of raising more funds for N.E.S.T. Project. 

After doing our research, we want to provide a professional, swift and a creatively collaborative process to get you a high quality piece of work that will help you land more roles. 

Included in our service:
- Initial consultation: We want to find out your strengths, what you want to achieve and the style that you want the reel to be. 

- Pitch: We go away and create a pitch for the scene to present back to you. A chance for you to have more input and craft a scene that intrigues you. 

- Development: Once you green light the pitch we go into deeper development, creating a script, specifically for you. 

- Character development: Before production, we will have a session with you, developing the character and diving deeper into the film. 

- Production: Lights, Camera, Action! Using our industry standard kit, we will create your reel to a standard so high that you will be walking away with your own short film. 

-Post Production: When we edit, we edit efficiently, using all industry standard software for editing, sound design and colour grading. 

And as a bonus, headshots will also be included in the package! 

We‚Äôre taking showreels to the next level, treating them as a short film that captures your voice as an artist! 

Get in touch - info@emberproduction.com - To book your showreel now!
